Traditionally, Celtic knotwork is drawn on a diagonal grid overlaid with
straight lines and circles.  Xamhain uses a much simpler method devised
by Andy Sloss, which divides the knot into sections at every other grid point.

If you want to know the details, you can find them in

    Andy Sloss
    How to Draw Celtic Knotwork: A Practical Handbook
    Cassell Illustrated, 2002 (New edition)
    ISBN 0304361259

You may also be interested in the website http://www.proscribe.co.uk/,
which features more work by Andy Sloss.
